# UI copy — humanized Title Case

User-facing **buttons**, **links**, **`<h1>`**, and **`<h2>`** (and matching
`CardTitle` / dialog titles at the same semantic level) use **Title Case**:
capitalize major words; keep articles/prepositions/conjunctions lowercase unless
first or last word (`Sign Up`, `Log In`, `Forgot Password?`, `Back to Dashboard`).

## Rules

- Prefer **Title Case** over sentence case for interactive and primary headings.
- Store copy in the feature's **`constants.ts`** (see `component-colocation.mdc`).
- Apply consistently: JSX text, `Button` children, `Link` children, toast
  messages triggered from that feature, and form submit labels.
- **Do not Title Case** body paragraphs, `CardDescription`, helper text, or
  long explanatory sentences — those stay sentence case.
- **No em dashes (`—`)** anywhere in user-facing copy (UI, toasts, emails,
  error messages). Use a comma, period, colon, or rephrase instead. Hyphens
  (`-`) are fine for compound words and kebab-case slugs shown as labels.
- Acronyms stay as-is (`OAuth`, `API`). Product name: `Cordial`.
- **DataTable column headers and toolbar filter labels** display as **ALL CAPS**.
  `DataTable` normalizes casing at render and in CSV export. Store readable
  Title Case in `COLUMN_*_HEADER` and filter label constants if you prefer;
  do not hand-uppercase per page.

## Examples

| ❌ Avoid | ✅ Use |
|----------|--------|
| Sign up | Sign Up |
| Log in | Log In |
| Create account | Create Account |
| Back to dashboard | Back to Dashboard |
| Send invite | Send Invite |
| No communities yet | No Communities Yet |
| Manage communities | Manage Communities |
| Continue with google | Continue with Google |
| Forums, discussions — member content | Forums and member content arrive later. |

```tsx
// LoginForm/constants.ts
export const TITLE = "Log In";
export const SUBMIT_LABEL = "Log In";
export const SIGNUP_LINK_LABEL = "Sign Up";
export const MAGIC_LINK_LABEL = "Email Me a Sign-In Link";

// index.tsx
import { TITLE, SUBMIT_LABEL } from "./constants";

<CardTitle>{TITLE}</CardTitle>
<Button type="submit">{SUBMIT_LABEL}</Button>
```

When adding or editing UI copy, fix nearby violations in the same file or
feature folder when reasonable.
